\textit{\textbf{\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!Kleene’ s Theorem:}} If R is an RE, then there exists an NDFA, $M_{NFA}$ with $\varepsilon$ transition, which accepts the
language generated by R.


\begin{flushleft}
\textsf{\textbf{5.5.2 Direct Conversion of RE to DFA}}
\end{flushleft}

\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!Using this method, a given RE is converted to a DFA without the construction of an NFA. Before
describing the process, we need to know a few defi nitions such as ‘fi rstpos’, ‘followpos’, ‘nullable’, and the construction processes of those.

\textsf{\textbf{\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!fi rstpos:}} It is the abbreviation of first position. It is defined as the set of the positions of the first symbols of strings generated by the sub-expression rooted by n.

\textsf{\textbf{\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!\!followpos:}} It is the abbreviation of follow position. It is defined as the set of the positions of the last symbols of strings generated by the sub-expression rooted by n.










